  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-01 04:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Intel Pivot + CRITICAL BUG FIX: OBI NameError Killing Trades\n\n**Task:** Investigate PM daily/weekly threshold markets for human copy targets (V6 opportunity). Instead found and fixed a critical trade-blocking bug.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **CRITICAL BUG FOUND & FIXED:** `NameError: name 'obi' is not defined` \u2014 crashing the bot during trade execution since Mar 30 12:43. The `obi`, `cvd`, `macd_h`, `vwap_val` variables were computed inside `check_conviction()` as local variables, but the indicator logging dict at line 557 in `should_trade()` tried to reference them directly. The bot crashed AFTER all filters passed, AFTER Kelly sizing, RIGHT BEFORE placing the order.\n   - **Impact:** 38 crashes logged. Every trade that passed all filters (bias, regime, conviction, edge, kelly) was KILLED at the last step. The Mar 31 11:15 trade that went through was likely during a window where the logging code wasn't reached (different code path).\n   - **Fix:** `check_conviction()` now stores indicators in `self._conviction_indicators`. The `_last_indicators` dict reads from there via `getattr(self, '_conviction_indicators', {})`.\n   - **Bot restarted** at 04:40 UTC, running clean. Syntax verified.\n\n2. **PM daily threshold market search \u2014 DEAD END:** Gamma API search is broken (returns same irrelevant results for every query). CLOB API only shows 4 ancient BTC markets (all at extreme prices like $17K, $1M). No active near-threshold daily/weekly BTC markets exist on PM right now. The V6 daily-market opportunity from yesterday's finding can't be tested \u2014 there are no markets to test on.\n\n3. **Copy Signal V2 (OBI monitor) is healthy:** Current net OBI = +0.058 (slightly bullish), confidence 11 (low). The orderbook data pipeline works \u2014 it's the indicator *logging* in the bot that was broken.\n\n**My thinking:**\n- This bug explains why we only got 1 trade on Mar 31 despite good conditions. The bot saw signals, passed all filters, then crashed on the indicator logging. The 11:15 trade might have succeeded because of a timing edge where the error was caught differently.\n- The 38 crash count means potentially 38 BLOCKED TRADES over Mar 30-31. Not all would have been real trades (many are retries of the same window), but several legitimate trades were killed.\n- This is WORSE than the zombie bug in some ways \u2014 the zombie caused duplicates, this one caused ZERO EXECUTION. It silently ate our trades.\n- V5a validation data from today will now be REAL \u2014 with the bug fixed, every trade that passes filters will actually execute and log indicators.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Bug FIXED and bot restarted. This is the #1 priority finding \u2014 supersedes copy intel research.\n- Today's active hours (11,12,19,20 UTC) will be the TRUE first test of V4.1 with working indicator logging\n- Daily markets for V6 copy intel: shelved until PM launches new BTC threshold markets\n- Need t",
